			    STPJS 241</div>
  <p class="cont">ance,<span class="footRef">1</span> but when men have sinned, there must be allowance made for them.<span class="footRef">2</span></p>
  <p class="std">All the religious world is boasting of righteousness; it is the doctrine of the devil to retard the
  human mind,<span class="footRef">3</span> and hinder our progress, by filling us with self-righteousness. The nearer we get to
  our heavenly Father, the more we are disposed to look with compassion on perishing souls;<span class="footRef">4</span> we feel
  that we want to take them upon our shoulders, and cast their sins behind our backs.<span class="footRef">5</span> My talk is
  intended for all this society; if you would have God have mercy on you,<span class="footRef">6</span> have mercy on one
  another.<span class="footRef">7</span></p>
  <p class="wideEllipse">* * *</p>

  <div class="topic">Men Cannot Be Compelled into Kingdom</div>
  <p class="std">He then made a promise in the name of the Lord, saying that that soul who has righteousness
  enough to ask God in the secret place<span class="footRef">8</span> for life, every day of their lives, shall live to three score years
  and ten. We must walk uprightly<span class="footRef">9</span> all the day long.<span class="footRef">10</span> How glorious are the principles of
  righteousness!<span class="footRef">11</span> We are full of selfishness;<span class="footRef">12</span> the devil flatters us<span class="footRef">13</span> that we are very righteous, when
  we are feeding on the faults of others.<span class="footRef">14</span> We can only live by worshiping 
  our God;<span class="footRef">15</span> all must do it for themselves; none can do it for another. How mild the Savior dealt with
  Peter, saying, &ldquo;When thou art converted, strengthen thy brethren.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">16</span> At another time, He said to him,
  &ldquo;Lovest thou me?&rdquo; and having received Peter&rsquo;s reply, He said, &ldquo;Feed my sheep.&rdquo;<span class="footRef">17</span> If the sisters
  loved the Lord, let them feed the sheep,<span class="footRef">18</span> and not destroy them.<span class="footRef">19</span> How oft have wise men and
  women sought to dictate Brother Joseph by saying, &ldquo;O, if I were Brother Joseph I would do this and
  that;&rdquo; but if they were in Brother Joseph&rsquo;s shoes they would find that men or women could not be
  compelled<span class="footRef">20</span> into the kingdom of God, but must be dealt with in long-suffering,<span class="footRef">21</span> and at last we shall
  save them. The way to keep all the Saints together, and keep the work rolling, is to wait with all
  long-suffering,<span class="footRef">22</span> till God shall bring such characters to justice. There should be no license for sin,
  but mercy should go hand in hand with reproof.<span class="footRef">23</span></p>
  <p class="std">Sisters of the society, shall there be strife among you?<span class="footRef">24</span> I will not have it. You must repent, and
  get the love of God.<span class="footRef">25</span> Away with self-righteousness!<span class="footRef">26</span> The best measure or principle to bring the
  poor to repentance is to administer to their wants.<span class="footRef">27</span></p>
